headline: Stock Market Today: Stocks Fall As Google, Tesla Earnings Loom; Netflix Dives On Results (Live Coverage)
summary: The Dow Jones Industrial Average pared its losses but couldn't get out of negative ground Friday as tariff concerns resurfaced with President Donald Trump reportedly pushing for steeper levies from the European Union.  Decliners on the stock market today included American Express while Google-parent Alphabet managed some gains.  The blue-chip index had stumbled by more than 200 points earlier after the Financial Times reported that Trump wants a minimum tariff of 15% to 20% on EU goods brought into U.S. The report, citing unnamed sources, said a 10% tariff on most items had been part of discussions regarding a framework trade agreement.

headline: IBKR jumps, Amex earnings, Union Pacific reportedly in deal talks
summary: Market Domination host Josh Lipton tracks today's top moving stocks in this Market Minute. Interactive Brokers (IBKR) shares rise after a strong second quarter earnings report, with Barclays citing a "clean quarter" and upbeat outlook amid a stable macro backdrop. American Express (AXP) also second quarter earnings beat, but flagged higher expenses. Meanwhile, Union Pacific (UNP) is reportedly in early talks to acquire rival Norfolk Southern (NSC), according to The Wall Street Journal. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

headline: Surge in Investor Trading Lifts Interactive Brokers’ Profits. The Stock Is Rising.
summary: Robust investor trading activity lifted  Interactive Brokers  second-quarter results as well as its stock price.  Shares of Interactive Brokers jumped 6% in pre-market trading Friday.  The stock price has doubled in the past year compared with a 14% one-year gain for the S&P 500.
